Race.SpecificTitle: PW Law Enforcement Dist. -- 5.77 Mills - Sheriff - 5 Yrs.
Race.FullText: Shall the Law Enforcement District of the Parish of West Feliciana, State of Louisiana (the "District"), continue to levy and collect five and seventy-seven hundredths (5.77) mills tax on all the property subject to taxation in the District (an estimated $1,552,000 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for an entire year), for a period of five (5) years, beginning with the year 2016 and ending with the year 2020, for the purpose of providing continued funding for the District?
